Effect of Salvia miltiorrhizae in the treatment of 36 infantile acute toxic myocarditis. Control observation of infantile acute toxic myocarditis treated by Salvia miltiorrhizae (SM) showed that 36 cases were clinically cured through SM treatment. The total effects have obvious advantages over Western Medicine control group, P < 0.01. The period of hospitalization and ECG normalization, of control group was significantly longer than that of SM treated group, P < 0.001 respectively.